res: Prove that the sum of the squares of the distances between any $n$ points on the unit sphere $\{(x, y, z) \mid x^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 1\}$ is at most $n^2$.
Translating: Prove that the sum of the squares of the distances between any $n$ points on the unit sphere $\{(x, y, z) \mid x^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 1\}$ is at most $n^2$.

res.typeView:
∀ {E : Type u} [inst : NormedAddCommGroup E] [inst_1 : InnerProductSpace ℝ E] [inst_2 : Module.Oriented ℝ E (Fin 3)]
  (s : Finset E), (∀ x ∈ s, ‖x‖ = 1) → ∑ x ∈ s, ∑ y ∈ s, dist x y ^ 2 ≤ ↑s.card ^ 2
